17/05/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government on Friday (14 May) approved the final package of judicial reform bills aimed at compliance with obligations undertaken in the course of EU accession talks.
Justice Minister Cristian Diaconescu said adoption of the laws would mark the successful completion of the process of harmonising the country's legislation with that of the EU.
The bills move next to parliament for discussion.
In other news, Turkish Justice Minister Cemil Cicek and Interior Minister Abdulkadir Aksu arrived on Monday for a two-day official visit to Romania.
They will attend the meeting of ministers of justice and home affairs of the Southeast European Co-operation Process.
(Anadolu Agency, Rompres, TRT 2 - 17/05/04)
